# phase 2 implementation

dgp,gate,sched,arch/s390x,lib,irq,build,docs: comprehensive authorization, fixup table, SCOMS migration, scheduler overhaul and QoL factors

sys/dgp: unified authorization chokepoint (dgp_authorize) with 34 operation kinds
         and per-operation rights mapping; deleted io_authority.cxxm (subsumed);
         decomposed admin god-bit into specific rights (lifecycle, delegate,
         quota, debug, sched, console, service); bootstrap_admin grants full
         rights set; lifecycle state removed from isolation_domain_state.

sys/gate: all nucleus call handlers (cap, dom, gate, io, mem, portal, sgn, sys)
          now route through dgp_authorize; cap_token validation added to I/O
          operations; gate_init/portal_init register domain teardown callbacks.

sys/domain: strand allocation via SCOMS table (not slab); strand_body for
        cold fields; idle_strand_create/destroy API; teardown callbacks
        for gate/portal drain; io_bind_txn RAII transaction.

sys/sched: cpu_timer_tick() hardware preemption via CPU timer interrupt;
           idle strands replace idle domains (SCOMS kobject_table);
           work stealing with proper lock ordering and vruntime normalization;
           sched_cpu_down properly drains fair tree and migrates strands;
           per-class admin rights use isolation_rights::sched.

sys/syschk: syschk_core updated to reference URL link for bug reports

arch/s390x/trap: exception/fixup table (EX_TABLE) with binary search in
                 trap/fixup.cxxm, link.ld .ex_table section, and precpp.hxx
                 macros; diagnose inline asm blocks EX_TABLE-protected with
                 register-pair overloads; lowcore struct access replaces
                 hardcoded addresses in ext/mcck/pgm handlers; pgm handler
                 now calls try_applying_fixup for supervisor-mode faults;
                 s390x_stack_frame renamed to stack_frame.

arch/s390x/lib: new arch-optimized cstring.cxx (MVC/XC/CLCLE/SRST/MVST/EXRL).

arch/s390x/cpu/diag: discrepancy between register_pair and u64 addressed using overloads.

sys/irqdesc: IRQ descriptor table migrated from pointer-table+slab to
             SCOMS kobject_table; irqdesc_init.cxxm deleted.

sys/mm/vm: vm_region allocation migrated from slab cache to SCOMS kobject_table.

sys/base/types: FixedSizeBase<Derived, Size>; std::byte emulation; usize/isize
                use __SIZE_TYPE__/__PTRDIFF_TYPE__; cxxabi disabled_wait→syschk_fatal.

scripts/patches: Update Hercules DIAG X'288' patch to address register handling, now mirroring
                 Linux expectations

sys/lib: cstring.cxxm rewritten to delegate to arch-specific __zx_* symbols;
         string_view uses __zx_memcmp; machine error codes extended (backlog, key);
         source_location returns "?" for unknown; Updated source_location formatter
         to format column and line as unsigned integer instead of char (bug).

build: ZX_TOOLCHAIN_FILE/ZX_CONFIG_FILE replace CMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE;
       artifact-dump target (disassemble + symbols); cmake/configs/base.cmake
       for default config; C/C++ extensions disabled; -fmacro-prefix-map.

misc/docs: BUG_LIST.{xml/xsd} for bug history management added; Doxyfile updated to reference
          crypto/ folder and standard C++ files.

misc/legal: CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md added;

misc/ci: updated workflows to use a newer version of Doxygen (requesting 1.15.0, was 1.9.x)

